The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for 3D skeleton-based action recognition, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs), convolutional neural networks (CNNs), and graph convolutional networks (GCNs), which are popular techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of large datasets and performance evaluation, which are common topics in neural networks (cs.NE) research.
